I think lthread (<a href="http://github.com/halayli/lthread" rel="nofollow">http://github.com/halayli/lthread</a>) is the only coroutine lib that allows you to block inside a coroutine and do heavy computation without affecting other coroutines.<p>Example:<p><pre><code>  void my_function(void* arg)
  {
      char buf[1024];

      int ret = lthread_recv_exact(fd, buf, 1024, 0, timeout);

      lthread_compute_begin();
      /* block as long as you wish, run heavy computation on buf, access your stack variables etc.. */

      lthread_compute_end();
  }
</code></pre>
